    "body": "Hi, experience the same problem as @jerryji .\r\n\r\neth.hashrate always returns 0 although --metrics is enabled.\r\n\r\nI start geth (for a private network ) like this:\r\n`\r\ngeth \\\r\n        --datadir $ETH_DIR/node-$nodeIndex/ \\\r\n        --identity 'node-'$nodeIndex \\\r\n        --networkid \"$NETWORK_ID\" \\\r\n        --ipcpath $node_ipcpath \\\r\n        --port $portValue \\\r\n        --rpc \\\r\n        --rpcaddr $rpcaddrValue \\\r\n        --rpcport $rpcportValue \\\r\n        --rpcapi $RPCAPI \\\r\n        --rpccorsdomain \"*\" \\\r\n        --ws \\\r\n        --wsaddr $wsaddrValue \\\r\n        --wsport $wsportValue \\\r\n        --wsapi $WSAPI \\\r\n        --wsorigins \"*\" \\\r\n        --bootnodes $bootnode_address \\\r\n        --ethstats $netstats_address \\\r\n        --gasprice $GAS_PRICE \\\r\n        --targetgaslimit $target_gas_limit \\\r\n        --unlock 0 \\\r\n        --password $ETH_DIR/node-$nodeIndex/password.txt \\\r\n        --etherbase 0 \\\r\n        --mine \\ #mining enabled\r\n        --metrics \\ #enabled for querying hashrate\r\n        --minerthreads 8 &\r\n`\r\nAm i missing something? I can see that geth is mining and everthing works as expected apart from eth.hashrate...\r\n",
